199template <class T>
200class Local {
201 public:
202 V8_INLINE Local() : val_(nullptr) {}
203 template <class S>
204 V8_INLINE Local(Local<S> that)
205 : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
211 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
212 }
213
217 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
218
222 V8_INLINE void Clear() { val_ = nullptr; }
223
224 V8_INLINE T* operator->() const { return val_; }
225
226 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return val_; }
227
238 template <class S>
239 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
240 internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_);
241 internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
242 if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
243 if (b == nullptr) return false;
244 return *a == *b;
245 }
246
247 template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator==(
248 const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
249 internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_);
250 internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
251 if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
252 if (b == nullptr) return false;
253 return *a == *b;
254 }
255
266 template <class S>
267 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Local<S>& that) const {
268 return !operator==(that);
269 }
270
271 template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator!=(
272 const Persistent<S>& that) const {
273 return !operator==(that);
274 }
275
281 template <class S> V8_INLINE static Local<T> Cast(Local<S> that) {
282#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
283 // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
284 // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
285 if (that.IsEmpty()) return Local<T>();
286#endif
287 return Local<T>(T::Cast(*that));
288 }
289
295 template <class S>
296 V8_INLINE Local<S> As() const {
297 return Local<S>::Cast(*this);
298 }
299
305 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, Local<T> that);
306 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate,
307 const PersistentBase<T>& that);
308 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate,
309 const BasicTracedReference<T>& that);
310
311 private:
312 friend class TracedReferenceBase;
313 friend class Utils;
314 template<class F> friend class Eternal;
315 template<class F> friend class PersistentBase;
316 template<class F, class M> friend class Persistent;
317 template<class F> friend class Local;
318 template <class F>
319 friend class MaybeLocal;
320 template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
321 template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
322 friend class String;
323 friend class Object;
324 friend class Context;
325 friend class Isolate;
326 friend class Private;
327 template<class F> friend class internal::CustomArguments;
328 friend Local<Primitive> Undefined(Isolate* isolate);
329 friend Local<Primitive> Null(Isolate* isolate);
330 friend Local<Boolean> True(Isolate* isolate);
331 friend Local<Boolean> False(Isolate* isolate);
332 friend class HandleScope;
333 friend class EscapableHandleScope;
334 template <class F1, class F2, class F3>
335 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
336 template<class F1, class F2> friend class PersistentValueVector;
337 template <class F>
338 friend class ReturnValue;
339 template <class F>
340 friend class Traced;
341 template <class F>
342 friend class TracedGlobal;
343 template <class F>
344 friend class BasicTracedReference;
345 template <class F>
346 friend class TracedReference;
347
348 explicit V8_INLINE Local(T* that) : val_(that) {}
349 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, T* that);
350 T* val_;
351};

371template <class T>
372class MaybeLocal {
373 public:
374 V8_INLINE MaybeLocal() : val_(nullptr) {}
375 template <class S>
376 V8_INLINE MaybeLocal(Local<S> that)
377 : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
378 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
379 }
380
381 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
382
387 template <class S>
388 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool ToLocal(Local<S>* out) const {
389 out->val_ = IsEmpty() ? nullptr : this->val_;
390 return !IsEmpty();
391 }
392
397 V8_INLINE Local<T> ToLocalChecked();
398
403 template <class S>
404 V8_INLINE Local<S> FromMaybe(Local<S> default_value) const {
405 return IsEmpty() ? default_value : Local<S>(val_);
406 }
407
408 private:
409 T* val_;
410};

433static const int kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
434static const int kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
435
436template <typename T>
437class WeakCallbackInfo {
438 public:
439 using Callback = void (*)(const WeakCallbackInfo<T>& data);
440
441 WeakCallbackInfo(Isolate* isolate, T* parameter,
442 void* embedder_fields[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback],
443 Callback* callback)
444 : isolate_(isolate), parameter_(parameter), callback_(callback) {
445 for (int i = 0; i < kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback; ++i) {
446 embedder_fields_[i] = embedder_fields[i];
447 }
448 }
449
450 V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
451 V8_INLINE T* GetParameter() const { return parameter_; }
452 V8_INLINE void* GetInternalField(int index) const;
453
454 // When first called, the embedder MUST Reset() the Global which triggered the
455 // callback. The Global itself is unusable for anything else. No v8 other api
456 // calls may be called in the first callback. Should additional work be
457 // required, the embedder must set a second pass callback, which will be
458 // called after all the initial callbacks are processed.
459 // Calling SetSecondPassCallback on the second pass will immediately crash.
460 void SetSecondPassCallback(Callback callback) const { *callback_ = callback; }
461
462 private:
463 Isolate* isolate_;
464 T* parameter_;
465 Callback* callback_;
466 void* embedder_fields_[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback];
467};
468
469
470// kParameter will pass a void* parameter back to the callback, kInternalFields
471// will pass the first two internal fields back to the callback, kFinalizer
472// will pass a void* parameter back, but is invoked before the object is
473// actually collected, so it can be resurrected. In the last case, it is not
474// possible to request a second pass callback.
475enum class WeakCallbackType { kParameter, kInternalFields, kFinalizer };

521 internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
522 if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
523 if (b == nullptr) return false;
524 return *a == *b;

526
527 template <class S>

530 internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
531 if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
532 if (b == nullptr) return false;
533 return *a == *b;
534 }
535

615 friend class Object;

620 T* val_;

668template <class T, class M> class Persistent : public PersistentBase<T> {
669 public:
673 V8_INLINE Persistent() : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {}
679 template <class S>
680 V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
681 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
682 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
683 }
689 template <class S, class M2>
690 V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, const Persistent<S, M2>& that)
691 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
692 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
693 }
700 V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent& that) : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {
701 Copy(that);
702 }
703 template <class S, class M2>
704 V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
705 Copy(that);
706 }
707 V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent& that) {
708 Copy(that);
709 return *this;
710 }
711 template <class S, class M2>
712 V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) { // NOLINT
713 Copy(that);
714 return *this;
715 }
721 V8_INLINE ~Persistent() {
722 if (M::kResetInDestructor) this->Reset();
723 }
724
725 // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
726 template <class S>
727 V8_INLINE static Persistent<T>& Cast(const Persistent<S>& that) { // NOLINT
728#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
729 // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
730 // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
731 if (!that.IsEmpty()) T::Cast(*that);
732#endif
733 return reinterpret_cast<Persistent<T>&>(const_cast<Persistent<S>&>(that));
734 }
735
736 // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
737 template <class S>
738 V8_INLINE Persistent<S>& As() const { // NOLINT
739 return Persistent<S>::Cast(*this);
740 }
741
742 private:
743 friend class Isolate;
744 friend class Utils;
745 template<class F> friend class Local;
746 template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
747 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
748
749 explicit V8_INLINE Persistent(T* that) : PersistentBase<T>(that) {}
750 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
751 template<class S, class M2>
752 V8_INLINE void Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that);
753};

834class TracedReferenceBase {
835 public:

841
846 V8_INLINE void Reset();
847
851 V8_INLINE v8::Local<v8::Value> Get(v8::Isolate* isolate) const;
852
857 bool IsEmptyThreadSafe() const {
858 return this->GetSlotThreadSafe() == nullptr;

860
864 V8_INLINE void SetWrapperClassId(uint16_t class_id);
865
870 V8_INLINE uint16_t WrapperClassId() const;
871
872 protected:
876 void SetSlotThreadSafe(void* new_val) {
877 reinterpret_cast<std::atomic<void*>*>(&val_)->store(
878 new_val, std::memory_order_relaxed);
879 }
880
884 const void* GetSlotThreadSafe() const {
885 return reinterpret_cast<std::atomic<const void*> const*>(&val_)->load(
886 std::memory_order_relaxed);
887 }
888
889 // val_ points to a GlobalHandles node.
890 internal::Address* val_ = nullptr;
891
892 friend class internal::BasicTracedReferenceExtractor;
893 template <typename F>
894 friend class Local;
895 template <typename U>
896 friend bool operator==(const TracedReferenceBase&, const Local<U>&);
897 friend bool operator==(const TracedReferenceBase&,
898 const TracedReferenceBase&);
899};

1390class ScriptOriginOptions {
1391 public:
1392 V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(bool is_shared_cross_origin = false,
1393 bool is_opaque = false, bool is_wasm = false,
1394 bool is_module = false)
1395 : flags_((is_shared_cross_origin ? kIsSharedCrossOrigin : 0) |
1396 (is_wasm ? kIsWasm : 0) | (is_opaque ? kIsOpaque : 0) |
1397 (is_module ? kIsModule : 0)) {}
1398 V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(int flags)
1399 : flags_(flags &
1400 (kIsSharedCrossOrigin | kIsOpaque | kIsWasm | kIsModule)) {}
1401
1402 bool IsSharedCrossOrigin() const {
1403 return (flags_ & kIsSharedCrossOrigin) != 0;
1404 }
1405 bool IsOpaque() const { return (flags_ & kIsOpaque) != 0; }
1406 bool IsWasm() const { return (flags_ & kIsWasm) != 0; }
1407 bool IsModule() const { return (flags_ & kIsModule) != 0; }
1408
1409 int Flags() const { return flags_; }
1410
1411 private:
1412 enum {
1413 kIsSharedCrossOrigin = 1,
1414 kIsOpaque = 1 << 1,
1415 kIsWasm = 1 << 2,
1416 kIsModule = 1 << 3
1417 };
1418 const int flags_;
1419};

1780class V8_EXPORT ScriptCompiler {
1781 public:
1789 struct V8_EXPORT CachedData {
1790 enum BufferPolicy {
1791 BufferNotOwned,
1792 BufferOwned
1793 };
1794
1795 CachedData()
1796 : data(nullptr),
1797 length(0),
1798 rejected(false),
1799 buffer_policy(BufferNotOwned) {}
1800
1801 // If buffer_policy is BufferNotOwned, the caller keeps the ownership of
1802 // data and guarantees that it stays alive until the CachedData object is
1803 // destroyed. If the policy is BufferOwned, the given data will be deleted
1804 // (with delete[]) when the CachedData object is destroyed.
1805 CachedData(const uint8_t* data, int length,
1806 BufferPolicy buffer_policy = BufferNotOwned);
1807 ~CachedData();
1808 // TODO(marja): Async compilation; add constructors which take a callback
1809 // which will be called when V8 no longer needs the data.
1810 const uint8_t* data;
1811 int length;
1812 bool rejected;
1813 BufferPolicy buffer_policy;
1814
1815 // Prevent copying.
1816 CachedData(const CachedData&) = delete;
1817 CachedData& operator=(const CachedData&) = delete;
1818 };

2366// Holds the callee saved registers needed for the stack unwinder. It is the
2367// empty struct if no registers are required. Implemented in
2368// include/v8-unwinder-state.h.
2369struct CalleeSavedRegisters;
2370
2371// A RegisterState represents the current state of registers used
2372// by the sampling profiler API.
2373struct V8_EXPORT RegisterState {
2374 RegisterState();
2375 ~RegisterState();
2376 RegisterState(const RegisterState& other);
2377 RegisterState& operator=(const RegisterState& other);
2378
2379 void* pc; // Instruction pointer.
2380 void* sp; // Stack pointer.
2381 void* fp; // Frame pointer.
2382 void* lr; // Link register (or nullptr on platforms without a link register).
2383 // Callee saved registers (or null if no callee saved registers were stored)
2384 std::unique_ptr<CalleeSavedRegisters> callee_saved;
2385};

3857 // Implements CreateDataProperty (ECMA-262, 7.3.4).
3858 //
3859 // Defines a configurable, writable, enumerable property with the given value
3860 // on the object unless the property already exists and is not configurable
3861 // or the object is not extensible.
3862 //
3863 // Returns true on success.

3868 uint32_t index,
3869 Local<Value> value);

3871 // Implements DefineOwnProperty.
3872 //
3873 // In general, CreateDataProperty will be faster, however, does not allow
3874 // for specifying attributes.
3875 //
3876 // Returns true on success.
3877 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT Maybe<bool> DefineOwnProperty(
3878 Local<Context> context, Local<Name> key, Local<Value> value,
3879 PropertyAttribute attributes = None);
3880
3881 // Implements Object.DefineProperty(O, P, Attributes), see Ecma-262 19.1.2.4.
3882 //
3883 // The defineProperty function is used to add an own property or
3884 // update the attributes of an existing own property of an object.
3885 //
3886 // Both data and accessor descriptors can be used.
3887 //
3888 // In general, CreateDataProperty is faster, however, does not allow
3889 // for specifying attributes or an accessor descriptor.
3890 //
3891 // The PropertyDescriptor can change when redefining a property.
3892 //
3893 // Returns true on success.
3894 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT Maybe<bool> DefineProperty(
3895 Local<Context> context, Local<Name> key,
3896 PropertyDescriptor& descriptor); // NOLINT(runtime/references)

4402template<typename T>
4403class ReturnValue {
4404 public:
4405 template <class S> V8_INLINE ReturnValue(const ReturnValue<S>& that)
4406 : value_(that.value_) {
4407 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
4408 }
4409 // Local setters
4410 template <typename S>
4411 V8_INLINE void Set(const Global<S>& handle);
4412 template <typename S>
4413 V8_INLINE void Set(const BasicTracedReference<S>& handle);
4414 template <typename S>
4415 V8_INLINE void Set(const Local<S> handle);
4416 // Fast primitive setters
4417 V8_INLINE void Set(bool value);
4418 V8_INLINE void Set(double i);
4419 V8_INLINE void Set(int32_t i);
4420 V8_INLINE void Set(uint32_t i);
4421 // Fast JS primitive setters
4422 V8_INLINE void SetNull();
4423 V8_INLINE void SetUndefined();
4424 V8_INLINE void SetEmptyString();
4425 // Convenience getter for Isolate
4426 V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const;
4427
4428 // Pointer setter: Uncompilable to prevent inadvertent misuse.
4429 template <typename S>
4430 V8_INLINE void Set(S* whatever);
4431
4432 // Getter. Creates a new Local<> so it comes with a certain performance
4433 // hit. If the ReturnValue was not yet set, this will return the undefined
4434 // value.
4435 V8_INLINE Local<Value> Get() const;
4436
4437 private:
4438 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
4439 template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
4440 template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
4441 template <class F, class G, class H>
4442 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
4443 V8_INLINE void SetInternal(internal::Address value) { *value_ = value; }
4444 V8_INLINE internal::Address GetDefaultValue();
4445 V8_INLINE explicit ReturnValue(internal::Address* slot);
4446 internal::Address* value_;
4447};

7885struct JitCodeEvent {
7886 enum EventType {
7887 CODE_ADDED,
7888 CODE_MOVED,
7889 CODE_REMOVED,
7890 CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO,
7891 CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING,
7892 CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING
7893 };
7894 // Definition of the code position type. The "POSITION" type means the place
7895 // in the source code which are of interest when making stack traces to
7896 // pin-point the source location of a stack frame as close as possible.
7897 // The "STATEMENT_POSITION" means the place at the beginning of each
7898 // statement, and is used to indicate possible break locations.
7899 enum PositionType { POSITION, STATEMENT_POSITION };
7900
7901 // There are two different kinds of JitCodeEvents, one for JIT code generated
7902 // by the optimizing compiler, and one for byte code generated for the
7903 // interpreter. For JIT_CODE events, the |code_start| member of the event
7904 // points to the beginning of jitted assembly code, while for BYTE_CODE
7905 // events, |code_start| points to the first bytecode of the interpreted
7906 // function.
7907 enum CodeType { BYTE_CODE, JIT_CODE };
7908
7909 // Type of event.
7910 EventType type;
7911 CodeType code_type;
7912 // Start of the instructions.
7913 void* code_start;
7914 // Size of the instructions.
7915 size_t code_len;
7916 // Script info for CODE_ADDED event.
7917 Local<UnboundScript> script;
7918 // User-defined data for *_LINE_INFO_* event. It's used to hold the source
7919 // code line information which is returned from the
7920 // CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING event. And it's passed to subsequent
7921 // CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO and CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING events.
7922 void* user_data;
7923
7924 struct name_t {
7925 // Name of the object associated with the code, note that the string is not
7926 // zero-terminated.
7927 const char* str;
7928 // Number of chars in str.
7929 size_t len;
7930 };
7931
7932 struct line_info_t {
7933 // PC offset
7934 size_t offset;
7935 // Code position
7936 size_t pos;
7937 // The position type.
7938 PositionType position_type;
7939 };
7940
7941 struct wasm_source_info_t {
7942 // Source file name.
7943 const char* filename;
7944 // Length of filename.
7945 size_t filename_size;
7946 // Line number table, which maps offsets of JITted code to line numbers of
7947 // source file.
7948 const line_info_t* line_number_table;
7949 // Number of entries in the line number table.
7950 size_t line_number_table_size;
7951 };
7952
7953 wasm_source_info_t* wasm_source_info;
7954
7955 union {
7956 // Only valid for CODE_ADDED.
7957 struct name_t name;
7958
7959 // Only valid for CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO
7960 struct line_info_t line_info;
7961
7962 // New location of instructions. Only valid for CODE_MOVED.
7963 void* new_code_start;
7964 };
7965
7966 Isolate* isolate;
7967};
7968
7974enum RAILMode : unsigned {
7975 // Response performance mode: In this mode very low virtual machine latency
7976 // is provided. V8 will try to avoid JavaScript execution interruptions.
7977 // Throughput may be throttled.
7978 PERFORMANCE_RESPONSE,
7979 // Animation performance mode: In this mode low virtual machine latency is
7980 // provided. V8 will try to avoid as many JavaScript execution interruptions
7981 // as possible. Throughput may be throttled. This is the default mode.
7982 PERFORMANCE_ANIMATION,
7983 // Idle performance mode: The embedder is idle. V8 can complete deferred work
7984 // in this mode.
7985 PERFORMANCE_IDLE,
7986 // Load performance mode: In this mode high throughput is provided. V8 may
7987 // turn off latency optimizations.
7988 PERFORMANCE_LOAD
7989};
7990
7994enum JitCodeEventOptions {
7995 kJitCodeEventDefault = 0,
7996 // Generate callbacks for already existent code.
7997 kJitCodeEventEnumExisting = 1
7998};

10142template <class T>
10143class Maybe {
10144 public:
10145 V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !has_value_; }
10146 V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return has_value_; }
10147
10151 V8_INLINE T ToChecked() const { return FromJust(); }
10152
10157 V8_INLINE void Check() const {
10158 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
10159 }
10160
10165 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool To(T* out) const {
10166 if (V8_LIKELY(IsJust())) *out = value_;
10167 return IsJust();
10168 }
10169
10174 V8_INLINE T FromJust() const {
10175 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
10176 return value_;
10177 }
10178
10183 V8_INLINE T FromMaybe(const T& default_value) const {
10184 return has_value_ ? value_ : default_value;
10185 }
10186
10187 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
10188 return (IsJust() == other.IsJust()) &&
10189 (!IsJust() || FromJust() == other.FromJust());
10190 }
10191
10192 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
10193 return !operator==(other);
10194 }
10195
10196 private:
10197 Maybe() : has_value_(false) {}
10198 explicit Maybe(const T& t) : has_value_(true), value_(t) {}
10199
10200 bool has_value_;
10201 T value_;
10202
10203 template <class U>
10204 friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
10205 template <class U>
10206 friend Maybe<U> Just(const U& u);
10207};
10208
10209template <class T>
10210inline Maybe<T> Nothing() {
10211 return Maybe<T>();
10212}
10213
10214template <class T>
10215inline Maybe<T> Just(const T& t) {
10216 return Maybe<T>(t);
10217}
10218
10219// A template specialization of Maybe<T> for the case of T = void.
10220template <>
10221class Maybe<void> {
10222 public:
10223 V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !is_valid_; }
10224 V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return is_valid_; }
10225
10226 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
10227 return IsJust() == other.IsJust();
10228 }
10229
10230 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
10231 return !operator==(other);
10232 }
10233
10234 private:
10235 struct JustTag {};
10236
10237 Maybe() : is_valid_(false) {}
10238 explicit Maybe(JustTag) : is_valid_(true) {}
10239
10240 bool is_valid_;
10241
10242 template <class U>
10243 friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
10244 friend Maybe<void> JustVoid();
10245};
10246
10247inline Maybe<void> JustVoid() { return Maybe<void>(Maybe<void>::JustTag()); }

10903template <class T>
10904Local<T> Local<T>::New(Isolate* isolate, Local<T> that) {
10905 return New(isolate, that.val_);
10906}
10907
10908template <class T>
10909Local<T> Local<T>::New(Isolate* isolate, const PersistentBase<T>& that) {
10910 return New(isolate, that.val_);
10911}
10912
10913template <class T>
10914Local<T> Local<T>::New(Isolate* isolate, const BasicTracedReference<T>& that) {
10915 return New(isolate, *that);
10916}
10917
10918template <class T>
10919Local<T> Local<T>::New(Isolate* isolate, T* that) {
10920 if (that == nullptr) return Local<T>();
10921 T* that_ptr = that;
10922 internal::Address* p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that_ptr);
10923 return Local<T>(reinterpret_cast<T*>(HandleScope::CreateHandle(
10924 reinterpret_cast<internal::Isolate*>(isolate), *p)));
10925}

10928template<class T>
10929template<class S>
10930void Eternal<T>::Set(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> handle) {
10931 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
10932 val_ = reinterpret_cast<T*>(
10933 V8::Eternalize(isolate, reinterpret_cast<Value*>(*handle)));
10934}
10935
10936template <class T>
10937Local<T> Eternal<T>::Get(Isolate* isolate) const {
10938 // The eternal handle will never go away, so as with the roots, we don't even
10939 // need to open a handle.
10940 return Local<T>(val_);
10941}

10945Local<T> MaybeLocal<T>::ToLocalChecked() {
10946 if (V8_UNLIKELY(val_ == nullptr)) V8::ToLocalEmpty();
10947 return Local<T>(val_);
10948}

10953#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
10954 if (index < 0 || index >= kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback) {
10955 V8::InternalFieldOutOfBounds(index);
10956 }
10957#endif

10964 if (that == nullptr) return nullptr;
10965 internal::Address* p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that);
10966 return reinterpret_cast<T*>(
10967 V8::GlobalizeReference(reinterpret_cast<internal::Isolate*>(isolate),
10968 p));
10969}

10972template <class T, class M>
10973template <class S, class M2>
10974void Persistent<T, M>::Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) {
10975 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
10976 this->Reset();
10977 if (that.IsEmpty()) return;
10978 internal::Address* p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
10979 this->val_ = reinterpret_cast<T*>(V8::CopyGlobalReference(p));
10980 M::Copy(that, this);
10981}

10986 if (this->IsEmpty()) return false;
10987 return I::GetNodeState(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_)) ==
10988 I::kNodeStateIsWeakValue;
10989}

11025 WeakCallbackType type) {
11026 using Callback = WeakCallbackInfo<void>::Callback;
11027#if (__GNUC__ >= 8) && !defined(__clang__)
11028#pragma GCC diagnostic push
11029#pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wcast-function-type"
11030#endif
11031 V8::MakeWeak(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_), parameter,
11032 reinterpret_cast<Callback>(callback), type);
11033#if (__GNUC__ >= 8) && !defined(__clang__)
11034#pragma GCC diagnostic pop
11035#endif
11036}

11075template <class T>
11076Global<T>::Global(Global&& other) : PersistentBase<T>(other.val_) {
11077 if (other.val_ != nullptr) {
11078 V8::MoveGlobalReference(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&other.val_),
11079 reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&this->val_));
11080 other.val_ = nullptr;
11081 }
11082}
11083
11084template <class T>
11085template <class S>
11086Global<T>& Global<T>::operator=(Global<S>&& rhs) {
11087 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
11088 if (this != &rhs) {
11089 this->Reset();
11090 if (rhs.val_ != nullptr) {
11091 this->val_ = rhs.val_;
11092 V8::MoveGlobalReference(
11093 reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&rhs.val_),
11094 reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&this->val_));
11095 rhs.val_ = nullptr;
11096 }
11097 }
11098 return *this;
11099}

11101template <class T>
11102internal::Address* BasicTracedReference<T>::New(
11103 Isolate* isolate, T* that, void* slot, DestructionMode destruction_mode) {
11104 if (that == nullptr) return nullptr;
11105 internal::Address* p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that);
11106 return V8::GlobalizeTracedReference(
11107 reinterpret_cast<internal::Isolate*>(isolate), p,
11108 reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(slot),
11109 destruction_mode == kWithDestructor);
11110}

11112void TracedReferenceBase::Reset() {
11113 if (IsEmpty()) return;
11114 V8::DisposeTracedGlobal(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(val_));
11115 SetSlotThreadSafe(nullptr);
11116}

11123V8_INLINE bool operator==(const TracedReferenceBase& lhs,
11124 const TracedReferenceBase& rhs) {
11125 v8::internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<v8::internal::Address*>(lhs.val_);
11126 v8::internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<v8::internal::Address*>(rhs.val_);
11127 if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
11128 if (b == nullptr) return false;
11129 return *a == *b;
11130}
11131
11132template <typename U>
11133V8_INLINE bool operator==(const TracedReferenceBase& lhs,
11134 const v8::Local<U>& rhs) {
11135 v8::internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<v8::internal::Address*>(lhs.val_);
11136 v8::internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<v8::internal::Address*>(*rhs);
11137 if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
11138 if (b == nullptr) return false;
11139 return *a == *b;
11140}

11328 Set(Number::New(GetIsolate(), i));

11330
11331template<typename T>
11332void ReturnValue<T>::Set(int32_t i) {
11333 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, Integer>::value, "type check");
11334 using I = internal::Internals;
11335 if (V8_LIKELY(I::IsValidSmi(i))) {
11336 *value_ = I::IntToSmi(i);
11337 return;
11338 }
11339 Set(Integer::New(GetIsolate(), i));
11340}
11341
11342template<typename T>
11343void ReturnValue<T>::Set(uint32_t i) {
11344 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, Integer>::value, "type check");
11345 // Can't simply use INT32_MAX here for whatever reason.
11346 bool fits_into_int32_t = (i & (1U << 31)) == 0;
11347 if (V8_LIKELY(fits_into_int32_t)) {
11348 Set(static_cast<int32_t>(i));
11349 return;
11350 }
11351 Set(Integer::NewFromUnsigned(GetIsolate(), i));
11352}
11353
11354template<typename T>
11355void ReturnValue<T>::Set(bool value) {
11356 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, Boolean>::value, "type check");
11357 using I = internal::Internals;
11358 int root_index;
11359 if (value) {
11360 root_index = I::kTrueValueRootIndex;
11361 } else {
11362 root_index = I::kFalseValueRootIndex;
11363 }
11364 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), root_index);
11365}
11366

11369 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, Primitive>::value, "type check");
11370 using I = internal::Internals;
11371 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kNullValueRootIndex);
11372}

11375void ReturnValue<T>::SetUndefined() {
11376 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, Primitive>::value, "type check");
11377 using I = internal::Internals;
11378 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kUndefinedValueRootIndex);
11379}

11388template <typename T>

11390 // Isolate is always the pointer below the default value on the stack.
11391 return *reinterpret_cast<Isolate**>(&value_[-2]);
11392}

11394template <typename T>
11395Local<Value> ReturnValue<T>::Get() const {
11396 using I = internal::Internals;
11397 if (*value_ == *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kTheHoleValueRootIndex))
11398 return Local<Value>(*Undefined(GetIsolate()));
11399 return Local<Value>::New(GetIsolate(), reinterpret_cast<Value*>(value_));
11400}

11424 return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(values_ + i));

11570 value);

11600
11601Local<Value> Object::GetInternalField(int index) {
11602#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11603 using A = internal::Address;
11604 using I = internal::Internals;
11605 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this);
11606 // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
11607 // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
11608 auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
11609 if (instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
11610 instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType ||
11611 instance_type == I::kJSSpecialApiObjectType) {
11612 int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
11613 A value = I::ReadRawField<A>(obj, offset);
11614#ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
11615 // We read the full pointer value and then decompress it in order to avoid
11616 // dealing with potential endiannes issues.
11617 value = I::DecompressTaggedAnyField(obj, static_cast<uint32_t>(value));
11618#endif
11619 internal::Isolate* isolate =
11620 internal::IsolateFromNeverReadOnlySpaceObject(obj);
11621 A* result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(isolate, value);
11622 return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
11623 }
11624#endif
11625 return SlowGetInternalField(index);
11626}
11627
11628
11629void* Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(int index) {
11630#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11631 using A = internal::Address;
11632 using I = internal::Internals;
11633 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this);
11634 // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
11635 // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
11636 auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
11637 if (V8_LIKELY(instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
11638 instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType ||
11639 instance_type == I::kJSSpecialApiObjectType)) {
11640 int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
11641#ifdef V8_HEAP_SANDBOX
11642 offset += I::kEmbedderDataSlotRawPayloadOffset;
11643#endif
11644 internal::Isolate* isolate = I::GetIsolateForHeapSandbox(obj);
11645 A value = I::ReadExternalPointerField(
11646 isolate, obj, offset, internal::kEmbedderDataSlotPayloadTag);
11647 return reinterpret_cast<void*>(value);
11648 }
11649#endif
11650 return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index);
11651}

11668
11669String::ExternalStringResource* String::GetExternalStringResource() const {
11670 using A = internal::Address;
11671 using I = internal::Internals;
11672 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11673
11674 ExternalStringResource* result;
11675 if (I::IsExternalTwoByteString(I::GetInstanceType(obj))) {
11676 internal::Isolate* isolate = I::GetIsolateForHeapSandbox(obj);
11677 A value =
11678 I::ReadExternalPointerField(isolate, obj, I::kStringResourceOffset,
11679 internal::kExternalStringResourceTag);
11680 result = reinterpret_cast<String::ExternalStringResource*>(value);
11681 } else {
11682 result = GetExternalStringResourceSlow();
11683 }
11684#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11685 VerifyExternalStringResource(result);
11686#endif
11687 return result;
11688}
11689
11690
11691String::ExternalStringResourceBase* String::GetExternalStringResourceBase(
11692 String::Encoding* encoding_out) const {
11693 using A = internal::Address;
11694 using I = internal::Internals;
11695 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11696 int type = I::GetInstanceType(obj) & I::kFullStringRepresentationMask;
11697 *encoding_out = static_cast<Encoding>(type & I::kStringEncodingMask);
11698 ExternalStringResourceBase* resource;
11699 if (type == I::kExternalOneByteRepresentationTag ||
11700 type == I::kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag) {
11701 internal::Isolate* isolate = I::GetIsolateForHeapSandbox(obj);
11702 A value =
11703 I::ReadExternalPointerField(isolate, obj, I::kStringResourceOffset,
11704 internal::kExternalStringResourceTag);
11705 resource = reinterpret_cast<ExternalStringResourceBase*>(value);
11706 } else {
11707 resource = GetExternalStringResourceBaseSlow(encoding_out);
11708 }
11709#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11710 VerifyExternalStringResourceBase(resource, *encoding_out);
11711#endif
11712 return resource;
11713}

11724bool Value::QuickIsUndefined() const {
11725 using A = internal::Address;
11726 using I = internal::Internals;
11727 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11728 if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
11729 if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
11730 return (I::GetOddballKind(obj) == I::kUndefinedOddballKind);
11731}

11758
11759bool Value::QuickIsNullOrUndefined() const {
11760 using A = internal::Address;
11761 using I = internal::Internals;
11762 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11763 if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
11764 if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
11765 int kind = I::GetOddballKind(obj);
11766 return kind == I::kNullOddballKind || kind == I::kUndefinedOddballKind;
11767}

12168template <typename T>

12172 I::IntToSmi(I::kInferShouldThrowMode)) {
12173 return args_[kShouldThrowOnErrorIndex] != I::IntToSmi(I::kDontThrow);

12176 reinterpret_cast<v8::internal::Isolate*>(GetIsolate()));

12238
12239Local<Value> Context::GetEmbedderData(int index) {
12240#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
12241 using A = internal::Address;
12242 using I = internal::Internals;
12243 A ctx = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
12244 A embedder_data =
12245 I::ReadTaggedPointerField(ctx, I::kNativeContextEmbedderDataOffset);
12246 int value_offset =
12247 I::kEmbedderDataArrayHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
12248 A value = I::ReadRawField<A>(embedder_data, value_offset);
12249#ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
12250 // We read the full pointer value and then decompress it in order to avoid
12251 // dealing with potential endiannes issues.
12252 value =
12253 I::DecompressTaggedAnyField(embedder_data, static_cast<uint32_t>(value));
12254#endif
12255 internal::Isolate* isolate = internal::IsolateFromNeverReadOnlySpaceObject(
12256 *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this));
12257 A* result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(isolate, value);
12258 return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
12259#else
12260 return SlowGetEmbedderData(index);
12261#endif
12262}
12263
12264
12265void* Context::GetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderData(int index) {
12266#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
12267 using A = internal::Address;
12268 using I = internal::Internals;
12269 A ctx = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
12270 A embedder_data =
12271 I::ReadTaggedPointerField(ctx, I::kNativeContextEmbedderDataOffset);
12272 int value_offset =
12273 I::kEmbedderDataArrayHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
12274#ifdef V8_HEAP_SANDBOX
12275 value_offset += I::kEmbedderDataSlotRawPayloadOffset;
12276#endif
12277 internal::Isolate* isolate = I::GetIsolateForHeapSandbox(ctx);
12278 return reinterpret_cast<void*>(
12279 I::ReadExternalPointerField(isolate, embedder_data, value_offset,
12280 internal::kEmbedderDataSlotPayloadTag));
12281#else
12282 return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderData(index);
12283#endif
12284}
12285
12286template <class T>
12287MaybeLocal<T> Context::GetDataFromSnapshotOnce(size_t index) {
12288 T* data = reinterpret_cast<T*>(GetDataFromSnapshotOnce(index));
12289 if (data) internal::PerformCastCheck(data);
12290 return Local<T>(data);
12291}

12293template <class T>
12294size_t SnapshotCreator::AddData(Local<Context> context, Local<T> object) {
12295 T* object_ptr = *object;
12296 internal::Address* p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(object_ptr);
12297 return AddData(context, *p);
12298}
